## **Tutorial 1: Basic Static Website**

This tutorial focuses on creating a simple, static website with a homepage, an about page, and a contact page.

### **Step 1: Set Up Your Project Structure**

Create a project folder with the following structure:

```
my-website/
│
├── index.html
├── about.html
├── contact.html
└── styles/
    └── styles.css
```

### **Step 2: Create the HTML Files**

**`index.html`**

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Home - My Website</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles/styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Welcome to My Website</h1>
        <nav>
            <a href="index.html">Home</a> |
            <a href="about.html">About</a> |
            <a href="contact.html">Contact</a>
        </nav>
    </header>
    <main>
        <p>This is the homepage of my simple website.</p>
    </main>
    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2023 My Website</p>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>
```

Repeat similar structures for `about.html` and `contact.html`, updating the `<title>`, `<h1>`, and `<main>` content accordingly.

### **Step 3: Add CSS Styling**

**`styles/styles.css`**

```css
