## **Tutorial 2: Responsive Single-Page Website**

This tutorial guides you to build a single-page website that's responsive across different devices.

### **Step 1: Initialize Project Structure**

Create a folder named `single-page-website` with:

```
single-page-website/
│
└── index.html
└── styles/
    └── styles.css
```

### **Step 2: Develop the HTML Structure**

**`index.html`**

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Single Page Site</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles/styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>My Single Page Website</h1>
        <nav>
            <a href="#home">Home</a> |
            <a href="#services">Services</a> |
            <a href="#contact">Contact</a>
        </nav>
    </header>

    <section id="home">
        <h2>Home</h2>
        <p>Welcome to my single-page website.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="services">
        <h2>Services</h2>
        <p>Details about services offered.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="contact">
        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>Contact information goes here.</p>
    </section>

    <footer>
        <p>&copy; 2023 Single Page Site</p>
    </footer>
</body>
</html>
```

### **Step 3: Implement Responsive CSS**

**`styles/styles.css`**

```css
