Your folder structure should look like this:

```
my-simple-website/
│
├── index.html
└── styles.css
```

## 3. Understanding the Basics of HTML

HTML (HyperText Markup Language) structures the content of your website. It uses tags to define elements like headings, paragraphs, links, images, etc.

### Basic HTML Structure

Here's the skeleton of an HTML document:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>My Simple Website</title>
</head>
<body>

</body>
</html>
```

- `<!DOCTYPE html>` declares the document type.
- `<html>` is the root element.
- `<head>` contains meta-information.
- `<body>` holds the content displayed on the page.

