## 9. Making It Responsive

Responsive design ensures your website looks good on all devices.

### Step 1: Add Meta Viewport Tag

Ensure you have the viewport meta tag in the `<head>`:

```html
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
```

### Step 2: Use Media Queries in CSS

```css
/* For devices with a width less than 600px */
@media (max-width: 600px) {
    nav ul {
        flex-direction: column;
    }

    nav ul li {
        margin: 10px 0;
    }

    footer {
        position: static;
    }
}
```

This media query adjusts the navigation layout and footer positioning on smaller screens.

